//@version=5
// AlgoFoundry — EXIT indicator (Take Profit on strong bearish close).
// Ported from your v5 strategy's "Take Profit Signal (strong close)".
//
// IMPORTANT FIX vs. your original: the take-profit condition no longer depends
// on this script's internal `isLong`. That gate would suppress the exit because
// this script never sees your (separate) entry signal — so it could never know
// you're long. The bridge is the source of truth for position state: it only
// acts on a SELL if you actually hold the symbol. So here we emit the SELL
// whenever the take-profit *condition* is true, stateless.
//
// Alert: one alert on this indicator, condition = "Any alert() function call",
// fire ONCE PER BAR CLOSE.
indicator(title="AlgoFoundry Exit — Take Profit (strong close)", overlay=true)

// === INPUTS ===
rsi_len = input.int(14, "RSI Length")
rsi_ob  = input.int(70, "RSI Overbought Level")
webhookSecret = input.string("PASTE_YOUR_SECRET_HERE", "Webhook secret")

// === TAKE PROFIT CONDITION ===
rsi = ta.rsi(close, rsi_len)
isOverbought       = ta.crossunder(rsi, rsi_ob)
strongBearishCandle = close < open and close < low[1]
takeProfitSignal   = isOverbought and strongBearishCandle   // no isLong gate

// === VISUALS ===
plotshape(takeProfitSignal, title="Take Profit", style=shape.triangledown, location=location.abovebar, size=size.small, color=color.purple)

// === ALERT (bar close only) ===
if takeProfitSignal and barstate.isconfirmed
    alert('{"action":"sell","symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '","secret":"' + webhookSecret + '"}', alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
